nASB</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>8</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11/15/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>7:34:37 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Lets get this done</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ok,<br>
<br>
We've been waffling for quite a while now, and because of it, BOTS is screaming FFA, and the Fear farmers are taking advantage...<br>
<br>
Lets agree to the rules:<br>
<br>
40 peeps<br>
<br>
at most 6 invites from any ONE guild<br>
<br>
1 day fear / 1 day hate / 2 days (shared if possible) sky<br>
<br>
Call in BB guilds for gods when you can't take them down, and if you don't, you lose your next date on the calendar AND that date is given (even if extra) to the BB guild who was next to be called in.<br>
<br>
Lets use the calendar under development with built in logic to prevent posting abuses.<br>
<br>
Lets rotate responsibility for following up on the rules between these posting entities, on a weekly basis, so no one person / guild is overly burdened with the enforcement of these policies.<br>
<br>
Lets not forget that we've more or less enjoyed these structured plane outings for quite some time now, and NOBODY can honestly say, they would prefer to zone into fear '/lfg = on' instead of breaking the planes with their friends and making an adventure of it...  Even the ubers appreciate this adventurous method of enjoying the planes.<br>
<br>
The 80-120 groupings, well, you don't have the extra days now under current rules, so its not like you're losing something you already have, AND with the 40 peeps rule, we should see some real limitation as to posting entities.  <br>
<br>
The vast majority of people concerned with the calendar are those of us who want our planar armor after waiting months and months and months, and it sure seems to me (not counting 3 / 4th chars) that the vast majority of the big guild's members say level 50+ have just about all their plane gear and/or kunark gear (ok, maybe not the paladins, JEEZ their drops suck.)<br>
<br>
If you analyze your numbers you may see that the number who need plane gear is probably not that much different from those in the 40-50 member groups who need gear.<br>
<br>
Further, we are only a few weeks away from a whole new expansion, and new planes.  Can't we coast out on these rules for now?  Honestly, those larger entities who have had their plane gear forever, and not going to be interested in fear / hate (other than epic mobs) and they'll be forging first into these new adventures.  Do we really want to set FFA precident for those new areas too, to the detriment of our shared progress into Velios?<br>
<br>
Lets just stop with the finger pointing, the acid posts, the flames, the recriminations.  Lets adopt these rules, and go have some fun.  Lets all go enjoy our plane adventures, lets all go get our gear, we've mired ourselves in this debate too long now.  Lets proceed.<br>
<br>
Zaron - Ranger of Silver Blade<br>
